{
  "video_id": "nz0cAjXVepg",
  "title": "Why we need to end the era of orphanages | Tara Winkler",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12641.0,
      "end_time": 16733.0,
      "text": "These are some photos of me volunteering in a Cambodian orphanage"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16757.0,
      "end_time": 17949.0,
      "text": "in 2006."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18660.0,
      "end_time": 20563.0,
      "text": "When these photos were taken,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20587.0,
      "end_time": 22889.0,
      "text": "I thought I was doing a really good thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22913.0,
      "end_time": 25421.0,
      "text": "and that I was really helping those kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26333.0,
      "end_time": 28244.0,
      "text": "I had a lot to learn."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29390.0,
      "end_time": 31835.0,
      "text": "It all started for me when I was 19 years old"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31859.0,
      "end_time": 34221.0,
      "text": "and went backpacking through Southeast Asia."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34863.0,
      "end_time": 36538.0,
      "text": "When I reached Cambodia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36562.0,
      "end_time": 40836.0,
      "text": "I felt uncomfortable being on holiday surrounded by so much poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 40860.0,
      "end_time": 42942.0,
      "text": "and wanted to do something to give back."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43695.0,
      "end_time": 47413.0,
      "text": "So I visited some orphanages and donated some clothes and books"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47437.0,
      "end_time": 48730.0,
      "text": "and some money"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48755.0,
      "end_time": 50534.0,
      "text": "to help the kids that I met."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51535.0,
      "end_time": 55687.0,
      "text": "But one of the orphanages I visited was desperately poor."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55711.0,
      "end_time": 59446.0,
      "text": "I had never encountered poverty like that before in my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59985.0,
      "end_time": 62394.0,
      "text": "They didn&#39;t have funds for enough food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62419.0,
      "end_time": 63729.0,
      "text": "clean water"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63753.0,
      "end_time": 65780.0,
      "text": "or medical treatment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65769.0,
      "end_time": 68667.0,
      "text": "and the sad little faces on those kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68691.0,
      "end_time": 69893.0,
      "text": "were heartbreaking."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 70550.0,
      "end_time": 73221.0,
      "text": "So I was compelled to do something more to help."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 74780.0,
      "end_time": 77742.0,
      "text": "I fund-raised in Australia and returned to Cambodia the following year"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77766.0,
      "end_time": 80243.0,
      "text": "to volunteer at the orphanage for a few months."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81195.0,
      "end_time": 84344.0,
      "text": "I taught English and bought water filters and food"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84368.0,
      "end_time": 88306.0,
      "text": "and took all of the kids to the dentist for the first time in their lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89307.0,
      "end_time": 91220.0,
      "text": "But over the course of the next year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91244.0,
      "end_time": 94828.0,
      "text": "I came to discover that this orphanage that I had been supporting"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 94852.0,
      "end_time": 96285.0,
      "text": "was terribly corrupt."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96934.0,
      "end_time": 101691.0,
      "text": "The director had been embezzling every cent donated to the orphanage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 101715.0,
      "end_time": 106650.0,
      "text": "and in my absence, the children were suffering such gross neglect"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106890.0,
      "end_time": 109138.0,
      "text": "that they were forced to catch mice to feed themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 110306.0,
      "end_time": 111709.0,
      "text": "I also found out later"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 111733.0,
      "end_time": 115467.0,
      "text": "that the director had been physically and sexually abusing the kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116703.0,
      "end_time": 119319.0,
      "text": "I couldn&#39;t bring myself to turn my back on children"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 119343.0,
      "end_time": 122500.0,
      "text": "who I had come to know and care about"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122290.0,
      "end_time": 124309.0,
      "text": "and return to my life in Australia."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124981.0,
      "end_time": 128518.0,
      "text": "So I worked with a local team and the local authorities"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 128542.0,
      "end_time": 131921.0,
      "text": "to set up a new orphanage and rescue the kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131945.0,
      "end_time": 134334.0,
      "text": "to give them a safe new home."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 136410.0,
      "end_time": 139743.0,
      "text": "But this is where my story takes another unexpected turn."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 140770.0,
      "end_time": 145825.0,
      "text": "As I adjusted to my new life running an orphanage in Cambodia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 146815.0,
      "end_time": 149389.0,
      "text": "(Khmer) I learned to speak Khmer fluently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 150797.0,
      "end_time": 154320.0,
      "text": "which means that I learned to speak the Khmer language fluently."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 154344.0,
      "end_time": 157394.0,
      "text": "And when I could communicate properly with the kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 157419.0,
      "end_time": 160650.0,
      "text": "I began to uncover some strange things."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 161517.0,
      "end_time": 165182.0,
      "text": "Most of the children we had removed from the orphanage"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 165206.0,
      "end_time": 168715.0,
      "text": "were not, in fact, orphans at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 169833.0,
      "end_time": 171310.0,
      "text": "They had parents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 172367.0,
      "end_time": 175738.0,
      "text": "and the few that were orphaned had other living relatives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 175762.0,
      "end_time": 178282.0,
      "text": "like grandparents and aunties and uncles"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 178306.0,
      "end_time": 179882.0,
      "text": "and other siblings."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 180705.0,
      "end_time": 185137.0,
      "text": "So why were these children living in an orphanage"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 185161.0,
      "end_time": 187507.0,
      "text": "when they weren&#39;t orphans?"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 189970.0,
      "end_time": 192331.0,
      "text": "Since 2005, the number of orphanages in Cambodia"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 192355.0,
      "end_time": 194778.0,
      "text": "has risen by 75 percent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 195596.0,
      "end_time": 198691.0,
      "text": "and the number of children living in Cambodian orphanages"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 198715.0,
      "end_time": 200861.0,
      "text": "has nearly doubled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 200885.0,
      "end_time": 202397.0,
      "text": "despite the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 202421.0,
      "end_time": 205543.0,
      "text": "that the vast majority of children living in these orphanages"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 205568.0,
      "end_time": 208550.0,
      "text": "are not orphans in the traditional sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 209970.0,
      "end_time": 211356.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re children from poor families."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 212711.0,
      "end_time": 215641.0,
      "text": "So if the vast majority of children living in orphanages"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 215665.0,
      "end_time": 217880.0,
      "text": "are not orphans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 217112.0,
      "end_time": 218974.0,
      "text": "then the term \"orphanage\""
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 218998.0,
      "end_time": 223656.0,
      "text": "is really just a euphemistic name for a residential care institution."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 224381.0,
      "end_time": 227314.0,
      "text": "These institutions go by other names as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 227338.0,
      "end_time": 232823.0,
      "text": "like \"shelters,\" \"safe houses,\" \"children&#39;s homes,\" \"children&#39;s villages,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 232847.0,
      "end_time": 234413.0,
      "text": "even \"boarding schools.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 235250.0,
      "end_time": 239271.0,
      "text": "And this problem is not just confined to Cambodia."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 240271.0,
      "end_time": 244610.0,
      "text": "This map shows some of the countries that have seen a dramatic increase"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 244860.0,
      "end_time": 246921.0,
      "text": "in the numbers of residential care institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 246945.0,
      "end_time": 250603.0,
      "text": "and the numbers of children being institutionalized."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 251627.0,
      "end_time": 253340.0,
      "text": "In Uganda, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 253580.0,
      "end_time": 255647.0,
      "text": "the number of children living in institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 255671.0,
      "end_time": 261400.0,
      "text": "has increased by more than 1,600 percent since 1992."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 262409.0,
      "end_time": 266829.0,
      "text": "And the problems posed by putting kids into institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 266853.0,
      "end_time": 271528.0,
      "text": "don&#39;t just pertain to the corrupt and abusive institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 271552.0,
      "end_time": 274207.0,
      "text": "like the one that I rescued the kids from."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 274231.0,
      "end_time": 278368.0,
      "text": "The problems are with all forms of residential care."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 279749.0,
      "end_time": 283755.0,
      "text": "Over 60 years of international research has shown us"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 283779.0,
      "end_time": 287940.0,
      "text": "that children who grow up in institutions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 287119.0,
      "end_time": 290630.0,
      "text": "even the very best institutions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 290870.0,
      "end_time": 293591.0,
      "text": "are at serious risk of developing mental illnesses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 293615.0,
      "end_time": 295398.0,
      "text": "attachment disorders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 295422.0,
      "end_time": 297653.0,
      "text": "growth and speech delays,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 297677.0,
      "end_time": 300641.0,
      "text": "and many will struggle with an inability to reintegrate"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 300665.0,
      "end_time": 302877.0,
      "text": "back into society later in life"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 302901.0,
      "end_time": 305568.0,
      "text": "and form healthy relationships as adults."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 306646.0,
      "end_time": 309834.0,
      "text": "These kids grow up without any model of family"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 309858.0,
      "end_time": 312305.0,
      "text": "or of what good parenting looks like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 312329.0,
      "end_time": 315468.0,
      "text": "so they then can struggle to parent their own children."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 316604.0,
      "end_time": 320721.0,
      "text": "So if you institutionalize large numbers of children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 320745.0,
      "end_time": 324282.0,
      "text": "it will affect not only this generation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 324306.0,
      "end_time": 326760.0,
      "text": "but also the generations to come."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 328366.0,
      "end_time": 331349.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve learned these lessons before in Australia."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 331881.0,
      "end_time": 335705.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s what happened to our \"Stolen Generations,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 335730.0,
      "end_time": 339388.0,
      "text": "the indigenous children who were removed from their families"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 339412.0,
      "end_time": 341832.0,
      "text": "with the belief that we could do a better job"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 341857.0,
      "end_time": 344100.0,
      "text": "of raising their children."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 345782.0,
      "end_time": 347305.0,
      "text": "Just imagine for a moment"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 347329.0,
      "end_time": 350870.0,
      "text": "what residential care would be like for a child."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 350843.0,
      "end_time": 354100.0,
      "text": "Firstly, you have a constant rotation of caregivers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 354250.0,
      "end_time": 357179.0,
      "text": "with somebody new coming on to the shift every eight hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 357739.0,
      "end_time": 360941.0,
      "text": "And then on top of that you have a steady stream of visitors"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 360966.0,
      "end_time": 362728.0,
      "text": "and volunteers coming in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 362752.0,
      "end_time": 365945.0,
      "text": "showering you in the love and affection you&#39;re craving"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 367410.0,
      "end_time": 368555.0,
      "text": "and then leaving again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 369157.0,
      "end_time": 372580.0,
      "text": "evoking all of those feelings of abandonment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 372830.0,
      "end_time": 375355.0,
      "text": "and proving again and again"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 375379.0,
      "end_time": 377818.0,
      "text": "that you are not worthy of being loved."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 379475.0,
      "end_time": 385273.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t have orphanages in Australia, the USA, the UK anymore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 385297.0,
      "end_time": 387253.0,
      "text": "and for a very good reason:"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 388175.0,
      "end_time": 391744.0,
      "text": "one study has shown that young adults raised in institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 391768.0,
      "end_time": 395686.0,
      "text": "are 10 times more likely to fall into sex work than their peers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 396298.0,
      "end_time": 399546.0,
      "text": "40 times more likely to have a criminal record,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 400586.0,
      "end_time": 404688.0,
      "text": "and 500 times more likely"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 404712.0,
      "end_time": 406591.0,
      "text": "to take their own lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 408623.0,
      "end_time": 413327.0,
      "text": "There are an estimated eight million children around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 413351.0,
      "end_time": 416375.0,
      "text": "living in institutions like orphanages,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 416399.0,
      "end_time": 420864.0,
      "text": "despite the fact that around 80 percent of them are not orphans."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 421623.0,
      "end_time": 424604.0,
      "text": "Most have families who could be caring for them"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 424628.0,
      "end_time": 426378.0,
      "text": "if they had the right support."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 428660.0,
      "end_time": 429311.0,
      "text": "But for me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 429975.0,
      "end_time": 432770.0,
      "text": "the most shocking thing of all to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 433325.0,
      "end_time": 435977.0,
      "text": "is what&#39;s contributing to this boom"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 436100.0,
      "end_time": 441250.0,
      "text": "in the unnecessary institutionalization of so many children:"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 443184.0,
      "end_time": 444428.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s us --"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 445576.0,
      "end_time": 448720.0,
      "text": "the tourists, the volunteers"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 449334.0,
      "end_time": 450689.0,
      "text": "and the donors."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 451783.0,
      "end_time": 457254.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the well-meaning support from people like me back in 2006,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 457278.0,
      "end_time": 461147.0,
      "text": "who visit these children and volunteer and donate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 461171.0,
      "end_time": 466270.0,
      "text": "who are unwittingly fueling an industry that exploits children"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 466294.0,
      "end_time": 468390.0,
      "text": "and tears families apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 469761.0,
      "end_time": 473539.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really no coincidence that these institutions are largely set up"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 473563.0,
      "end_time": 476474.0,
      "text": "in areas where tourists can most easily be lured in"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 476499.0,
      "end_time": 480872.0,
      "text": "to visit and volunteer in exchange for donations."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 481744.0,
      "end_time": 485178.0,
      "text": "Of the 600 so-called orphanages in Nepal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 485869.0,
      "end_time": 490649.0,
      "text": "over 90 percent of them are located in the most popular tourist hotspots."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 492222.0,
      "end_time": 494435.0,
      "text": "The cold, hard truth is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 494459.0,
      "end_time": 498802.0,
      "text": "the more money that floods in in support of these institutions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 498826.0,
      "end_time": 501150.0,
      "text": "the more institutions open"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 501715.0,
      "end_time": 504861.0,
      "text": "and the more children are removed from their families"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 504885.0,
      "end_time": 506397.0,
      "text": "to fill their beds."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 507550.0,
      "end_time": 510477.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just the laws of supply and demand."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 512433.0,
      "end_time": 515570.0,
      "text": "I had to learn all of these lessons the hard way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 515595.0,
      "end_time": 519281.0,
      "text": "after I had already set up an orphanage in Cambodia."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 520297.0,
      "end_time": 523503.0,
      "text": "I had to eat a big piece of humble pie to admit"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 524289.0,
      "end_time": 526694.0,
      "text": "that I had made a mistake"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 526718.0,
      "end_time": 529559.0,
      "text": "and inadvertently become a part of the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 530634.0,
      "end_time": 532962.0,
      "text": "I had been an orphanage tourist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 532986.0,
      "end_time": 534847.0,
      "text": "a voluntourist."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 534871.0,
      "end_time": 539853.0,
      "text": "I then set up my own orphanage and facilitated orphanage tourism"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 539878.0,
      "end_time": 542527.0,
      "text": "in order to generate funds for my orphanage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 543281.0,
      "end_time": 544885.0,
      "text": "before I knew better."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 546195.0,
      "end_time": 548203.0,
      "text": "What I came to learn"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 548227.0,
      "end_time": 551637.0,
      "text": "is that no matter how good my orphanage was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 551661.0,
      "end_time": 556315.0,
      "text": "it was never going to give those kids what they really needed:"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 557769.0,
      "end_time": 559269.0,
      "text": "their families."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 561118.0,
      "end_time": 564137.0,
      "text": "I know that it can feel incredibly depressing"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 564161.0,
      "end_time": 567915.0,
      "text": "to learn that helping vulnerable children and overcoming poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 567940.0,
      "end_time": 571479.0,
      "text": "is not as simple as we&#39;ve all been led to believe it should be."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 572741.0,
      "end_time": 575763.0,
      "text": "But thankfully, there is a solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 576484.0,
      "end_time": 580282.0,
      "text": "These problems are reversible and preventable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 580306.0,
      "end_time": 582320.0,
      "text": "and when we know better,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 582344.0,
      "end_time": 583739.0,
      "text": "we can do better."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 584913.0,
      "end_time": 587261.0,
      "text": "The organization that I run today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 587285.0,
      "end_time": 589557.0,
      "text": "the Cambodian Children&#39;s Trust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 589581.0,
      "end_time": 591609.0,
      "text": "is no longer an orphanage."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 592255.0,
      "end_time": 597978.0,
      "text": "In 2012, we changed the model in favor of family-based care."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 598891.0,
      "end_time": 602682.0,
      "text": "I now lead an amazing team of Cambodian social workers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 602706.0,
      "end_time": 604266.0,
      "text": "nurses and teachers."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 604803.0,
      "end_time": 607208.0,
      "text": "Together, we work within communities"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 607232.0,
      "end_time": 610545.0,
      "text": "to untangle a complex web of social issues"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 610570.0,
      "end_time": 613575.0,
      "text": "and help Cambodian families escape poverty."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 614595.0,
      "end_time": 618753.0,
      "text": "Our primary focus is on preventing some of the most vulnerable families"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 618777.0,
      "end_time": 619938.0,
      "text": "in our community"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 619962.0,
      "end_time": 622348.0,
      "text": "from being separated in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 623314.0,
      "end_time": 625347.0,
      "text": "But in cases where it&#39;s not possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 625371.0,
      "end_time": 628625.0,
      "text": "for a child to live with its biological family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 628649.0,
      "end_time": 630791.0,
      "text": "we support them in foster care."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 631990.0,
      "end_time": 635657.0,
      "text": "Family-based care is always better"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 635681.0,
      "end_time": 638775.0,
      "text": "than placing a child in an institution."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 640293.0,
      "end_time": 643700.0,
      "text": "Do you remember that first photo that I showed you before?"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 643875.0,
      "end_time": 647180.0,
      "text": "See that girl who is just about to catch the ball?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 647420.0,
      "end_time": 648579.0,
      "text": "Her name is Torn"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 649283.0,
      "end_time": 652586.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s a strong, brave and fiercely intelligent girl."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 653157.0,
      "end_time": 656520.0,
      "text": "But in 2006, when I first met her"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 656760.0,
      "end_time": 659107.0,
      "text": "living in that corrupt and abusive orphanage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 659869.0,
      "end_time": 661569.0,
      "text": "she had never been to school."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 662193.0,
      "end_time": 664260.0,
      "text": "She was suffering terrible neglect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 664957.0,
      "end_time": 667793.0,
      "text": "and she yearned desperately"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 667817.0,
      "end_time": 670533.0,
      "text": "for the warmth and love of her mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 672354.0,
      "end_time": 676438.0,
      "text": "But this is a photo of Torn today with her family."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 676462.0,
      "end_time": 678876.0,
      "text": "Her mother now has a secure job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 678900.0,
      "end_time": 681424.0,
      "text": "her siblings are doing well in high school"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 681448.0,
      "end_time": 685356.0,
      "text": "and she is just about to finish her nursing degree at university."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 685928.0,
      "end_time": 687499.0,
      "text": "For Torn&#39;s family --"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 687523.0,
      "end_time": 694521.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 696570.0,
      "end_time": 697462.0,
      "text": "for Torn&#39;s family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 697486.0,
      "end_time": 700760.0,
      "text": "the cycle of poverty has been broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 701910.0,
      "end_time": 704763.0,
      "text": "The family-based care model that we have developed at CCT"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 704787.0,
      "end_time": 706596.0,
      "text": "has been so successful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 706620.0,
      "end_time": 709998.0,
      "text": "that it&#39;s now being put forward by UNICEF Cambodia"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 710220.0,
      "end_time": 711538.0,
      "text": "and the Cambodian government"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 711562.0,
      "end_time": 715635.0,
      "text": "as a national solution to keep children in families."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 716936.0,
      "end_time": 718293.0,
      "text": "And one of the best --"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 718721.0,
      "end_time": 722706.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 724484.0,
      "end_time": 728826.0,
      "text": "And one of the best ways that you can help to solve this problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 728850.0,
      "end_time": 732646.0,
      "text": "is by giving these eight million children a voice"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 732670.0,
      "end_time": 735562.0,
      "text": "and become an advocate for family-based care."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 736358.0,
      "end_time": 739459.0,
      "text": "If we work together to raise awareness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 739484.0,
      "end_time": 742320.0,
      "text": "we can make sure the world knows"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 742344.0,
      "end_time": 747452.0,
      "text": "that we need to put an end to the unnecessary institutionalization"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 747476.0,
      "end_time": 749136.0,
      "text": "of vulnerable children."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 749973.0,
      "end_time": 751540.0,
      "text": "How do we achieve that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 752140.0,
      "end_time": 755841.0,
      "text": "By redirecting our support and our donations"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 755865.0,
      "end_time": 760191.0,
      "text": "away from orphanages and residential care institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 760215.0,
      "end_time": 766293.0,
      "text": "towards organizations that are committed to keeping children in families."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 767384.0,
      "end_time": 770803.0,
      "text": "I believe we can make this happen in our lifetime,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 770827.0,
      "end_time": 774470.0,
      "text": "and as a result, we will see developing communities thrive"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 774494.0,
      "end_time": 777687.0,
      "text": "and ensure that vulnerable children everywhere"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 777711.0,
      "end_time": 781687.0,
      "text": "have what all children need and deserve:"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 782468.0,
      "end_time": 783854.0,
      "text": "a family."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 783879.0,
      "end_time": 785590.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 785830.0,
      "end_time": 789410.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}